================================================================================
Third-party dependencies (not bundled; installed via pip)
================================================================================

- Ultralytics YOLO (`ultralytics`) — AGPL-3.0-or-later.
  https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics
  IMPORTANT: ultralytics is the DEFAULT detector backend and is copyleft
  (AGPL-3.0). This project's own code is Apache-2.0, but combining or deploying
  it together with ultralytics subjects that combined work to the AGPL-3.0,
  including its network-use (SaaS) obligations. The detector adapter interface
  (proving_ground/adapters/base.py) lets you substitute a differently-licensed
  detector if you need to avoid AGPL terms.

- PyTorch (`torch`, `torchvision`) — BSD-3-Clause.
- OpenCV (`opencv-python-headless`) — Apache-2.0.
- NumPy (`numpy`) — BSD-3-Clause.

The COCO class-name strings are used as detection labels.

